### Git Workflow for Repos

- Each repository under `repos/` is an independent git working tree.
- Commit changes in each repo independently using `cd {{range $i, $r := .BmadRepos}}{{if eq $i 0}}{{$r.ContainerPath}}{{end}}{{end}}` (or the appropriate repo path).
- Git push is still blocked in all repositories — code review happens on the host.
- Use relative paths from `/workspace` when referencing files across repos.
{{- end}}

## Best Practices

- Commit changes frequently with descriptive messages.
- Do not attempt to push — all code review happens on the host.
- Use inner containers for service dependencies (databases, caches, etc.).
- Run tests inside the sandbox to validate changes before signaling completion.
